      "position": 7,
      "content": "The Legal Studies program at UC Santa Cruz welcomes transfer students. Although not required for admission, students are encouraged to complete one lower-division course listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below before transferring. Students are also encouraged to complete the California General Education Transfer Curriculum (Cal-GETC) or all UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring. For guidance on incorporating Cal-GETC into your academic plan, consult your community college counselor. Please visit the Legal Studies website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Legal Studies B.A. Program Statement",
